results.name: Numbers k for which bigomega(sigma(k)) < bigomega(k), where bigomega (A001222) gives the number of prime factors with multiplicity, and sigma (A000203) gives the sum of divisors.
comment: Numbers k such that A058063(k) < A001222(k).
If terms x and y are present and gcd(x,y) = 1, then x*y is present also. This follows because both A001222 and A058063 are additive sequences, their difference A336386 is also.
xref: Positions of negative terms in A336386.
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Jul 20 2020
